page.title: 16ECONOMICS
page.content: Woburn Sands has two Banks in the High Street, Barclays and Nat.West. In addition there are banking facilities for members of the Co-operative Bank at the local Co-op shop. The Post Office operates a National Savings Bank facility and Girobank. There are also agencie of the Gateway, Halifax and Nationwide Building Societies. Yesterday we went to the NatWest Bank and while we were waiting to go inside Nathan pressed a fifty pound button. Mrs Porter had said not to touch anything. The manager showed us to a room where they type letters, then we went to see the safe. The walls, floor and ceiling are concrete. They have 3000 customers.(Michelle) You can be a member of the Little Extra Club.You get lots of good things and a card on your birthday.(Amy)
